ry.go\\n\\nThen check recent PRs on the repo for any review comments that might be relevant:\\n- gh pr list --repo entireio/cli --state merged --limit 10 --json number,title\\n- For relevant PRs, check: gh api repos/entireio/cli/pulls/{number}/comments --jq '.[].body'\\n\\nLook for review feedback patterns that might also apply to PR #362.\\n\\nReturn any issues found. If no relevant past comments apply, say so explicitly.\",\"agentId\":\"a448858\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VTn6jMwLc3YxzeHv8FCfbj\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01U9ruPsZQaV9LU8vcW6xJkV\",\"uuid\":\"321704f4-9262-4286-849f-b13924a8f4e2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T05:03:19.306Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"321704f4-9262-4286-849f-b13924a8f4e2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"d2c445ae-9204-4579-be05-a68b4745a770\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"update_enable\",\"slug\":\"playful-stirring-cascade\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DmhB1FNKg1oJy3eFbM7gPN\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"`ireturn` linter is enabled, and returning an interface type here will fail lint unless explicitly allowed. Please restore the prior `//nolint:ireturn` (with an explanation) or add `strategy.Strategy` to the ireturn allow-list in `.golangci.yaml`.\\nSame as above: `Default()` returns the `Strategy` interface, which will trigger the `ireturn` linter (enabled in `.golangci.yaml`) now that the `//nolint:ireturn` annotation was removed.\\n`NewManualCommitStrategy()` returns the `Strategy` interface. With `ireturn` enabled, this will fail lint unless you keep `//nolint:ireturn` (with explanation) or allow this return type in `.golangci.yaml`.\\nThe error text says \\\"not found or empty\\\", but `fileExists()` only checks `os.Stat` (existence), not file size/content. Either update the message to only mention \\\"not found\\\" or extend the check to verify the transcript file is non-empty before proceeding.\\n```suggestion\\n\\tif transcriptRef == \\\"\\\" {\\n\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"transcript file not found or empty: %s\\\", transcriptRef)\\n\\t}\\n\\tinfo, err := os.Stat(transcriptRef)\\n\\tif err != nil || info.Size() == 0 {\\n\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"transcript file not found or empty: %s\\\", transcriptRef)\\n\\t}\\n```\\n`newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging` supports injected stdin via `cmd.InOrStdin()`, but this handler always reads from `os.Stdin`, which makes it harder to test and inconsistent with the rest of the hook command plumbing. Consider threading an `io.Reader` through (or using `cmd.InOrStdin()` at the call site) so PostTodo can be exercised in unit tests.\\n`NewShadowStrategy()` returns the `Strategy` interface and will trigger the `ireturn` linter now that the `//nolint:ireturn` annotation was removed. Please restore the nolint (with explanation) or update the ireturn allow-list.\\n`NewAutoCommitStrategy()` returns the `Strategy` interface. Since `ireturn` is enabled, removing `//nolint:ireturn` here likely breaks lint/CI. Please restore the annotation (with explanation) or allow this type in `.golangci.yaml`.\\n```suggestion\\n// NewAutoCommitStrategy creates a new AutoCommitStrategy instance.\\n//\\n//nolint:ireturn // Factory intentionally returns Strategy interface as part of the strategy pattern.\\n```\\nThis comment is now inaccurate: `handleLifecycleCompaction` does not call `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` first. Also, the test currently ignores the handler error and doesn't assert that `CheckpointTranscriptStart` was reset, so it will pass even if the compaction reset regresses.\\n```suggestion\\n\\t// Run compaction and verify it succeeds in this test setup.\\n\\t// This test specifically ensures that compaction resets the transcript offset.\\n\\tif err := handleLifecycleCompaction(ag, event); err != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"handleLifecycleCompaction returned error: %v\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Load session state and check if offset was reset to 0\\n\\tloadedState, err := strategy.LoadSessionState(sessionID)\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"Failed to load session state: %v\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\tif loadedState == nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"Expected non-nil session state for session %q\\\", sessionID)\\n\\t}\\n\\tif loadedState.CheckpointTranscriptStart != 0 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"Expected CheckpointTranscriptStart to be 0 after compaction, got %d\\\",\\n```\\nThe test should assert the behavior it claims to validate. After calling `handleLifecycleCompaction`, consider requiring that the loaded session state is non-nil and `CheckpointTranscriptStart == 0` (and failing the test otherwise).\\n```suggestion\\n\\t// Run compaction and require it to succeed.\\n\\tif err := handleLifecycleCompaction(ag, event); err != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"handleLifecycleCompaction returned error: %v\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Load session state and verify the transcript offset has been reset.\\n\\tloadedState, err := strategy.LoadSessionState(sessionID)\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"failed to load session state: %v\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\tif loadedState == nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected non-nil session state after compaction for session %q\\\", sessionID)\\n\\t}\\n\\tif loadedState.CheckpointTranscriptStart != 0 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected CheckpointTranscriptStart to be 0 after compaction, got %d\\\",\\n```\\n### TurnEnd misses files modified by subagents\\n\\n**High Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\nThe old `commitWithMetadata` called `claudecode.ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptPath, transcriptOffset, subagentsDir)` which scanned both the main transcript and all subagent transcripts in the subagents directory. The new generic `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` only calls `analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(transcriptRef, transcriptOffset)`, which for Claude Code only reads the main transcript file. Files modified by subagents during the turn are no longer included in the `ModifiedFiles` list for the TurnEnd checkpoint, resulting in incomplete checkpoint metadata and potentially missed files in strategy processing.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: 0e77fd80-660c-4a42-bb34-3b1828617854 -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L226-L234\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\n### Subagent token usage excluded with empty directory\\n\\n**Medium Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\n`CalculateTokenUsage` passes an empty string for the `subagentsDir` parameter to `CalculateTotalTokenUsage`. The old code computed the actual subagents directory path and passed it, so token usage from subagent sessions was included. The comment on line 128 acknowledges this gap (\\\"For now, compute subagentsDir from the transcript path structure\\\") but then passes `\\\"\\\"` instead of actually computing it. This results in underreported token counts for sessions using Claude Code subagents.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: d80e1cf8-748a-4281-96ec-3d134b59701c -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go#L123-L130\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\n### Sentinel timestamp check removes upper bound validation\\n\\n**Low Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\nThe new `checkStopSentinel` only checks that the sentinel timestamp is after `hookStartTime - maxSkew`, removing the upper bound check (`ts.Before(hookStartTime.Add(maxSkew))`) that existed in the old implementation. This means any sentinel with a sufficiently recent timestamp will match, even one from a concurrent or future stop hook invocation, weakening the staleness protection.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: b0a576c1-d5c2-40d8-a4ea-2cda621a74c1 -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go#L309-L312\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\nFor Claude Code, subagent transcripts are expected under `<transcriptDir>/<modelSessionID>/subagents/agent-<id>.jsonl` (see existing strategy logic/tests). Computing `subagentsDir` as `<transcriptDir>/subagents` will prevent including subagent-modified files and token usage in checkpoints. Consider deriving the directory using the model session ID (event.SessionID) or delegating subagent transcript location resolution to the agent implementation.\\n```suggestion\\n\\t// Compute subagents directory for agents that support subagent extraction.\\n\\t// Subagent transcripts are expected under <transcriptDir>/<modelSessionID>/subagents/.\\n\\tsubagentsDir := filepath.Join(sessionDir, \\\"subagents\\\")\\n```\\n`CapturePrePromptState` no longer populates `LastTranscriptIdentifier`, but later `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` reads it and passes it into `StepContext.StepTranscriptIdentifier`. This means checkpoints will always store an empty transcript identifier, which is likely to break any rewind/resume logic that depe