sitives. The code checks for `.husky/` directory existence, but Husky v5+ uses `.husky/_` as its marker directory. A project could have a `.husky/` directory for unrelated purposes. Consider adding a separate field to hookManager for the detection path vs. the hook directory path. For Husky, detect using `.husky/_` but reference `.husky/` in warning messages. This would make detection more accurate while keeping user-facing messages correct.\\nThe example comment \\\"e.g. '.husky/' → '.husky/'\\\" doesn't add clarity since input and output are identical. Consider clarifying the purpose, such as \\\"Use the config path as the hook directory prefix. For Husky, this is '.husky/' where hook files are stored.\\\"\\n```suggestion\\n\\t\\t\\t// Use the config path as the hook directory prefix for hook files.\\n\\t\\t\\t// For Husky, this is typically \\\".husky/\\\" where hook scripts are stored.\\n```\\nPresence of .husky/_ dir means that .husky/ dir also exists. This is an acceptable false positive.\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"uuid\":\"a3c29c34-6fa7-4bb8-a7fb-febf589a5f88\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T05:03:20.105Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"You are reviewing PR #362 in entireio/cli by checking past PRs that touched the same files.\\n\\nThe main files modified are:\\n- cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/setup.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/setup_test.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/registry.go\\n\\nFor each file, find recent PRs that touched it. Use:\\n- git log --oneline -10 -- cmd/entire/cli/setup.go\\n- git log --oneline -10 -- cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go\\n\\nThen check recent PRs on the repo for any review comments that might be relevant:\\n- gh pr list --repo entireio/cli --state merged --limit 10 --json number,title\\n- For relevant PRs, check: gh api repos/entireio/cli/pulls/{number}/comments --jq '.[].body'\\n\\nLook for review feedback patterns that might also apply to PR #362.\\n\\nReturn any issues found. If