oth \\\"1\\\" and \\\"0\\\")\\nThis function is critical for determining whether to show interactive prompts, so proper test coverage is important.\\nRemoving the `//nolint:ireturn` comment will cause linter failures unless `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy.Strategy` is added to the `ireturn.allow` list in `.golangci.yaml`. The `ireturn` linter is enabled and `strategy.Strategy` is not currently in the allow list (only `agent.Agent` is). This same issue applies to all the strategy factory functions where the nolint comment was removed.\\nRemoving the `//nolint:ireturn` comment will cause linter failures unless `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy.Strategy` is added to the `ireturn.allow` list in `.golangci.yaml`.\\n```suggestion\\n// Falls back to returning nil if no strategies are registered.\\n//nolint:ireturn // Default intentionally returns the Strategy interface\\n```\\n### Agent prompt disabled on Windows terminals\\n\\n**Medium Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\n`canPromptInteractively` checks only `/dev/tty`, which does not exist on Windows. That makes the function always return false there, so `detectOrSelectAgent` never shows the new agent-selection prompt and silently falls back to `agent.Default()`. Windows users can be configured with the wrong agent.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: dc105156-7339-44a5-92eb-d1b31d4febab -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/setup.go#L590-L594\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\n### Agent autodetection is non-deterministic\\n\\n**Low Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\n`detectOrSelectAgent` accepts the first result from `agent.Detect()`. Detection iterates registered agents from a map, so when both `.claude` and `.gemini` are present the selected agent can vary between runs. This can install different hook sets for the same repository without any user choice.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: ref1_b22ed217-fe70-406b-9047-75851a191b57 -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/setup.go#L514-L518\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></p>\\n\\n\\n`agent.Detect()` iterates over the internal registry map, so if multiple agents report presence (e.g., both `.claude/` and `.gemini/` exist) the detected agent is nondeterministic. That can lead to installing hooks for the wrong agent. Consider making detection deterministic (iterate `agent.List()` and check `DetectPresence()` in a stable order) and/or handling the \\\"multiple agents detected\\\" case by prompting the user instead of picking an arbitrary one.\\n`canPromptInteractively()` currently relies on opening `/dev/tty`. This bypasses the project's ACCESSIBLE mode (where huh can read from stdin instead of `/dev/tty`) and will always return false on platforms without `/dev/tty` (e.g., Windows), preventing the new agent-selection UX from ever showing. Consider using a cross-platform terminal check (e.g., `x/term` or `go-isatty`) and treating ACCESSIBLE mode as prompt-capable when stdin is available, rather than hard-coding `/dev/tty`.\\n`TestDetectOrSelectAgent_NoDetection_WithTTY_ShowsPromptMessages` calls `detectOrSelectAgent()` with `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1`, which will run `form.Run()` and can block waiting for interactive input when tests are executed from a real terminal (or behave differently under ACCESSIBLE mode). This makes the unit test potentially hanging/flaky. To keep tests non-interactive, consider refactoring `detectOrSelectAgent` to inject/mock the selection prompt, or avoid executing `form.Run()` in unit tests (e.g., gate prompting behind a test-only flag and test the prompt path via integration tests with a pty).\\n```suggestion\\n\\t// This test previously forced the interactive TTY prompt path by setting\\n\\t// ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1 and calling detectOrSelectAgent, which can block on\\n\\t// form.Run() when a real TTY is present. Interactive behavior is better\\n\\t// exercised via integration tests using a pty, so we skip this at the\\n\\t// unit-test level to keep the suite strictly non-interactive.\\n\\tt.Skip(\\\"Interactive TTY prompt behavior is covered by integration tests with a pty\\\")\\n```\\nwe dont support windows today\\nwe don't support windows today\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"uuid\":\"2eeff242-9902-43e2-92f8-2e7649997089\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T05:03:26.032Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"You are reviewing PR #362 in entireio/cli by checking past PRs that touched the same files.\\n\\nThe main files modified are:\\n- cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/setup.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/setup_test.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/registry.go\\n\\nFor each file, find recent PRs that touched it. Use:\\n- git log --oneline -10 -- cmd/entire/cli/setup.go\\n- git log --oneline -10 -- cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go\\n\\nThen check recent PRs on the repo for any review comments that might be relevant:\\n- gh pr list --repo entireio/cli --state merged --limit 10 --json number,title\\n- For relevant PRs, check: gh api repos/entireio/cli/pulls/{number}/comments --jq '.[].body'\\n\\nLook for review feedback patterns that might also apply to PR #362.\\n\\nReturn any issues found. If no relevant past comments apply, say so explicitly.\",\"agentId\":\"a448858\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VTn6jMwLc3YxzeHv8FCfbj\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01U9ruPsZQaV9LU8vcW6xJkV\",\"uuid\":\"21db76f0-fb36-4a2f-81ad-2d8f05fd4682\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T05:03:26.033Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"21db76f0-fb36-4a2f-81ad-2d8f05fd4682\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"d2c445ae-9204-4579-be05-a68b4745a770\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"update_enable\",\"slug\":\"playful-stirring-cascade\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T05:03:28.755Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_012cQcQ