horough assessment. Here is my report:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## PR #362 Review: Relevant Past Feedback Patterns\\n\\n### Files Changed Summary\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` — Added `DetectAll()`, refactored `Detect()` to use it, making detection deterministic (sorted order).\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` — Added `detectOrSelectAgent()`, `setupAgentHooks()`, `canPromptInteractively()`; replaced the old single-agent-always-Claude-Code setup with multi-agent detection/selection.\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/setup_test.go` — New tests for the above functions.\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/registry.go` — Cosmetic only: removed two blank `//` separator comment lines before `func Default()`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Issues Found from Past Review Patterns\\n\\n**1. `ireturn` linter concern — DOES NOT APPLY to this PR**\\n\\nPR #360 had multiple comments flagging that removing `//nolint:ireturn` from strategy factory functions would break the linter. This was a live issue in PR #360. In PR #362's `strategy/registry.go`, the only change is removing two blank comment lines (`//` and blank line) before `func Default()` — the function signature itself is untouched and `strategy.Strategy` is already in the `ireturn.allow` list in `.golangci.yaml`. No lint breakage here.\\n\\n**2. Non-deterministic agent detection — ADDRESSED in this PR**\\n\\nPR #362's review comments on `agent/registry.go` flagged that the old `Detect()` iterated a map (non-deterministic). This PR correctly fixes it: `DetectAll()` calls `List()` which returns sorted names, so iteration is now deterministic. The past review concern does not apply — it was fixed in this PR.\\n\\n**3. `canPromptInteractively()` uses `/dev/tty` hardcode — RELEVANT past feedback, acknowledged by maintainers**\\n\\nFrom existing PR #362 review comments: one reviewer flagged that `/dev/tty` won't work on Windows and suggested using `golang.org/x/term` or `go-isatty`. The maintainer response was: \\\"we don't support windows today.\\\" This is a doc